"In the home, you will be promised one, and on arrival you will be cheated, your passports will be taken away and you will not receive the promised wage," confirms the head of the Main Administration for Labour Migration of the Tajik Migration Authority, Tolib Schwaripow.
Don't shrink, boss!
Nevertheless, many citizens of the Central Asian republics who want to make their money in Russia admit not only to dominate the language of the target country, but also to hardly express themselves in writing in their own language.
Of course, this is not so much their fault as the evil: only a few Turkmen, Uzbekistan and Tadjik can afford a reasonable basic education.
