It must be susceptible to various neighbours and opinions, and that is not easy.
Now the US's influence in European policy is constantly decreasing, but the EU is not filling this vacuum at the moment, who else remains there?
The Germans will simply have to play a bigger role.
Even if they don't like it, it's unpleasant for them and makes it much more unpleasant - it's life!
