The 6th summit of the Presidents of the Union of South American Nations (Unasur) ended today in Peru without publication of the Lima Declaration, which was previously announced and had to be theoretically signed by the seven present governors.
Efe repeatedly tried to obtain access to the signed document at the VI. Ordinary meeting of the Heads of State and Government of the Unasur. Sources at the State and Presidential Office initially informed that they would hand it over after the clause, but subsequently declared that it would be published on the website of the Peruvian Government for some time.
