Journalists had limited access to information on the summit at any time.
During the day, only the image of the presidential meeting without sound was transmitted in the press room with the message "private meeting, limited audio".
The few information circulated among the journalists were received by the press speakers of some of the governments of the Unasur present at the meeting, but not by the Peruvian press speaker.
The only document that was disseminated during the day was the list of participating presidents, which caused discomfort among hundreds of journalists from different national and international media who asked for more information.
Subsequently, the Presidential Office of Peru sent the media an e-mail with the "final declaration" of the summit, but it was the Humala declaration and not the official document on the conclusion of the summit.
